Package gameWorld.rooms

Class Room

java.lang.Object
gameWorld.rooms.Room
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
MobRoom, ShopRoom, SpawnRoom
public class Room
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
A room, is a place that the Hero can move , and that is surrounded by some Wall. It can also have adjacent Room next to it that are accessible via a Door.

The Room holds a lot of variable, most of them being list of precise GameObjects that are present in the room, like the TearList or the WallList ... . The Room also has an Hero inside of it.

The List of NonStaticObject is mainly used by the makeTearPLay() function as a way to know everything that the Tear can harm in the Room.

Usually a Room is created with a child class and not directly with the Room's constructor.

Their are a lot of different type of Room to check them you can check, SpawnRoom, MobRoom, ShopRoom and BossRoom.
